Settings description
__________________________________________________________________

 * |OVP_DocBegin_BoxAlgorithm_DownsamplingGPL_Settings|
 * |OVP_DocEnd_BoxAlgorithm_DownsamplingGPL_Settings|
 *
 * |OVP_DocBegin_BoxAlgorithm_DownsamplingGPL_Setting1|
 * New sampling rate in Hz chosen to downsample the input signal.
 * |OVP_DocEnd_BoxAlgorithm_DownsamplingGPL_Setting1|
 *
 * |OVP_DocBegin_BoxAlgorithm_DownsamplingGPL_Setting2|
 * Select the frequency cutoff of the low-pass filter as a ratio (1/2,
 * 1/3 or 1/4) of the new sampling rate.
 * |OVP_DocEnd_BoxAlgorithm_DownsamplingGPL_Setting2|
 *
 * |OVP_DocBegin_BoxAlgorithm_DownsamplingGPL_Setting3|
 * Select the kind of filter between Butterworth, Chebychev and Yule-Walker.
 * |OVP_DocEnd_BoxAlgorithm_DownsamplingGPL_Setting3|
 *
 * |OVP_DocBegin_BoxAlgorithm_DownsamplingGPL_Setting4|
 * Order of the low-pass filter.
 * |OVP_DocEnd_BoxAlgorithm_DownsamplingGPL_Setting4|
 *
 * |OVP_DocBegin_BoxAlgorithm_DownsamplingGPL_Setting5|
 * If Chebychev filter is selected, PassBand Ripple is a necessary info.
 * |OVP_DocEnd_BoxAlgorithm_DownsamplingGPL_Setting5|
__________________________________________________________________

Examples description
__________________________________________________________________

 * |OVP_DocBegin_BoxAlgorithm_DownsamplingGPL_Examples|
 * Let's consider our input signal sampling rate is 1 kHz.
 * If the new selected sampling rate is 200 Hz and the Frequency
 * cutoff ratio is 1/4, then a low-pass filter (with freqeuncy
 * cutoff equal to 200*1/4 = 50 Hz) is applied  before downsampling
 * at 200 Hz.
 * |OVP_DocEnd_BoxAlgorithm_DownsamplingGPL_Examples|
__________________________________________________________________

